Informasi segmen

Segmen adalah komponen yang dapat dibedakan dari Grup yang terlibat baik dalam menyediakan produk-produk tenentu (segmen usaha), atau dalam menyediakan produk dalam lingkungan ekonomi tertentu (segmen geograﬁs), yang memiliki risiko dan imbalan yang berbeda dari segmen lainnya.

Pendapatan, beban, hasil, aset dan liabilitas segmen termasuk hal-hal yang dapat diatribusikan secara Iangsung kepada suatu segmen serta haI-hal yang dapat dialokasikan dengan dasar yang memadai untuk segmen tersebut. Segmen ditentukan sebelum saldo dan transaksi antar perusahaan dieliminasi.

Kontijensi

Kewajiban kontijensi tidak diakui dalam Iaporan keuangan konsolidasian tetapi disajikan dalam catatan alas Iaporan keuangan konsolidasian kecuali jika kemungkinan arus keluar sumber daya yang memiliki manfaat ekonomi sangat kecil. Aset kontijensi tidak diakui dalam Iaporan keuangan konsolidasian tetapi disajikan dalam catatan kepada laporan keuangan konsolidasian apabila ada kemungkinan arus masuk manfaat ekonomi.

Peristiwa setelah periode laporan keuangan

Peristiwa setelah tanggal periode Iaporan yang memberikan informasi tambahan terkait posisi Grup saat periode laporan keuangan (adjusting events) disajikan dalam laporan keuangan konsolidasian. Peristiwa setelah tanggal periode Iaporan keuangan yang bukan adjusting events telah disajikan dalam catatan alas laporan keuangan konsolidasian apabila material.

Earnings (loss) per share

Basic earnings/loss per share are calculated by dividing proﬂt/loss tor the year attributable to ordinary equity holders of the parent by the weighted average number of ordinary shares outstanding during the year, after considering treasury stock.

Diluted earnings/Ioss per share amounts are calculated by dividing the proﬁtﬂoss attributable to ordinary equity holder of the parent by the weighted average number of ordinary shares outstanding during the year, after considering treasury stock plus the weighted average number of ordinary shares that would be issued on conversion of all the dilutive potential ordinary shares into ordinary shares.

Segment information

A segment is a distinguishable component of the Group that is engaged either in providing certain products (business segment), or in providing products within a particular economic environment (geographical segment), which is subject to risks and rewards that are different from those of other segments.

Segment revenue, expenses, results, assets and liabilities include items directly attributable to a segment as well as those that can be allocated on a reasonable basis to that segment. They are determined before intragroup balances and intragroup transactions are eliminated,

Contingencies

Contingent liabilities are not recognized in the consolidated ﬁnancial statements but are disclosed in the notes to the consolidated ﬁnancial statements unless the possibility of an outﬂow of resources embodying economic beneﬁts is remote. Contingent assets are not recognized in the consolidated ﬁnancial statements but are disclosed in the notes to the consolidated ﬁnancial statements when an inﬂow of economic beneﬁts is probable.

Events after the ﬁnancial reporting period

Events after the end of ﬁnancial reporting date that provide additional information about the Group’s position at reporting period (adjusting events) are reﬂected in the consolidated ﬁnancial statements. Subsequent events aﬂer the end of ﬁnancial reporting date that are not adjusting events are disclosed in the notes to the consolidated ﬁnancial statements when material.
